# VERSION
v0.17.0

# Changelog
- v0.17.0
    - **DuPont analysis page wired to artemis backend**
        - Replaced the hard-coded mock data in `dupont-analysis.page.ts` with live data from `ArtemisBiService.getDupont()` → artemis `GET /bi/dupont/{symbol}`. First BI analysis page to consume a real artemis computation endpoint. Canvas layout, connectors, operators, and styles are unchanged.
        - Added a period-kind selector (default TTM), a reporting-period selector, and a Q3 extrapolation checkbox (only shown for YTD + 三季报). A view toggle switches between actual YTD and predicted full-year (Q3 YTD × 4/3) when extrapolation is enabled.
        - Reporting-period options filter by kind: annual only lists 年报 (12-31); other kinds list all periods. Selecting an incompatible period auto-falls back to "最新" to avoid 404s.
        - Headline driver cards now show the prior-period value alongside the delta/direction; tree nodes show the delta. Prior period renders only when available.
        - Added a "ROE 取数与计算说明" panel at the bottom documenting each period kind's numerator/denominator, the Q3 extrapolation rule, and the DuPont identity.
        - Extended `ArtemisBiService.getDupont()` and `bi-simple.models.ts` with `period_kind`, `target_reporting_period`, `extrapolate_q4`, and `extrapolated_full_year`. Symbol is hard-coded to 000021 (深科技) for this first integration.
- v0.16.2
    - **BI static financial analysis dashboards**
        - Added a static DuPont analysis page with hard-coded mock data, tree-style decomposition, trend indicators, and balance-sheet linkage.
        - Added a static financial summary page with KPI cards, period comparison values, a metric selector, metric value comparison, trend comparison, cash-flow, balance-structure, expense, and tax sections.
        - Added a financial ability analysis menu group with nested entries for profitability, growth, operating, and solvency analysis.
        - Added the first financial ability dashboard: profitability analysis, including KPI cards, benchmark values, radar-style peer comparison, a trend selector, and a detail table.
        - Added placeholder pages for the remaining financial ability subpages so the new nested navigation has stable routes.
    - **BI navigation and layout updates**
        - Extended the side-menu model and application layout to support nested menu items while preserving existing flat menu behavior.
        - Registered missing Ant Design icons used by the top navigation to avoid runtime icon errors.
        - Increased the Angular component style budget for Cthulhu so richer static BI dashboard styling can build without changing page structure.
    - **BI dashboard readability**
        - Increased small auxiliary text sizes across the financial summary and profitability dashboards, including comparison deltas, period labels, legends, chart labels, panel notes, and tables.
- v0.16.1
    - **Raw data explorer: enum rendering + routing fixes**
        - **Enum code → label_zh rendering**: `formatCell(v, field?)` now consults a per-dataset `enumMaps` cache (pre-fetched once per field list via `ArtemisBiService.getEnum`) and renders the enum label instead of the raw code. Added `enum_ref?` to `BIFieldMeta`.
        - **Enum cache in `ArtemisBiService`**: `getEnum()` now caches by `enumName:source` so repeat dataset views don't re-fetch.
        - **Routing fix in `raw-data-explorer.page.ts`**: added `buildQuery()` dispatcher so corporate_action hits `/bi/corporate-action/...` and equity_structure hits `/bi/equity-structure/...` instead of always calling `queryFinancial()`.
        - **Conditional filters**: report_type/statement_code selectors only show for `financial_statement`; equity_structure shows 变动日 date range labels.
        - **Default `statement_code` = null** (was `'1'`) so profit_express/profit_notice rows with empty `statement_code` aren't filtered out.
        - **Removed `progress_code` auto-preselect** for corporate_action per user feedback — fields start unselected.
- v0.16.0
    - **BI module redesign: 3-layer UI over artemis/phoenixA**
        - **Removed legacy BI code**:
            - Deleted old BI pages except `bi-overview.page.ts` and `bi-shell.component.ts`
            - Deleted `features/bi/services/bi-api.service.ts`
            - Deleted `features/bi/models/bi.models.ts`
        - **Added new BI layer**:
            - New `features/bi/services/artemis-bi.service.ts`: API client for artemis `/bi/*`
            - New `features/bi/pages/stock-list.page.ts`: paginated stock list (layer 1)
            - New `features/bi/pages/company-overview.page.ts`: company overview with datasets (layer 2)
            - New `features/bi/pages/raw-data-explorer.page.ts`: raw data explorer with native HTML controls (layer 3)
            - Updated `features/bi/bi.routes.ts`: new route structure
            - No YoY/QoQ computation in frontend — only raw data display
        - **Fixed company overview labels**:
            - Corrected display text for dataset availability
- v0.15.3
    - **BI second/third iteration: trend interaction upgrade**
        - Added reusable trend control component `ui/trend-controls.component.ts` for `季度/年度` view switch + `12/16/20` period selector.
        - Updated `financial-dashboard.page.ts` to support trend controls and pass selected view options to all trend charts.
        - Updated `financial-quality.page.ts` to support the same controls and align table rows with selected annual/quarterly mode + period window.
        - Added local persistence for trend preferences via `localStorage` key `bi-trend-settings` for cross-page consistency.
    - **BI chart behavior improvements**
        - Enhanced `trend-chart.component.ts` to apply annual filtering and period tail slicing while preserving chronological rendering.
        - Added test coverage `trend-chart.component.spec.ts` for chronological ordering, annual filtering, and period window behavior.
- v0.15.2
    - Updated Cthulhu BI charting:
        - Trend chart now defensively reorders to chronological periods.
        - Added chart zoom controls for long-horizon series.
        - DuPont page now renders recursive tree-style decomposition instead of flat cards.
- v0.15.1
    - **Fix BI navigation parameter issue**
        - Fixed issue where navigating from Company Financial Entry page to BI detail pages would redirect back to entry page
        - Changed parameter access from `this.route.snapshot.paramMap.get('symbol')` to `this.route.parent?.paramMap.pipe(first()).subscribe()`
        - This ensures child components can correctly access the `:symbol` parameter from parent route `/bi/financial/company/:symbol`
        - Fixed by using RxJS `first()` operator to take only the first emission and proper parameter lookup
    - **BI bug fixes and improvements**
        - Fixed nested route parameter access issue where child components couldn't read parent route `symbol` parameter
        - Added symbol validation in all BI page components - redirects to entry page when symbol is missing
        - Added proper error handling with user-friendly error messages in all BI pages
        - Backend now validates symbol parameter and returns 400 error for empty/invalid symbols
        - Added "返回" (Back) button on error pages for better UX
- v0.15.0
      - **BI MVP frontend module**
          - Added new top-level `BI` feature route group under `/bi`
          - Added BI top-nav entry so the module is discoverable from the main product navigation
          - Added BI pages:
              - `BI Overview`
              - `Company Financial Entry`
              - `Company Financial Overview`
              - `Dupont Analysis`
              - `Financial Quality`
              - `Metric Dictionary`
          - Added BI API client wired to Artemis `/bi/*` endpoints
          - Added company context header component for shared BI company metadata display
          - Current scope is BI-only and intentionally excludes Atlas / narrative integration
      - **Frontend validation & tests**
          - Added `bi-api.service.spec.ts` for Artemis BI HTTP contract coverage
          - Added `company-context-bar.component.spec.ts` for BI company header rendering coverage
          - Updated outdated base tests (`AppComponent`, `AppLayoutComponent`) so the Angular suite matches the current app shell / icon runtime behavior
          - Verified Cthulhu frontend tests pass: `12 SUCCESS`
          - Verified Angular build succeeds with BI lazy route chunk generation
- v0.14.0
      - **Factor Engine follow-up usability fixes**
          - Availability tab now shows hoverable `?` help on `Live`, `Expected`, `Source Readiness`, `Capability source`, `Selected source`, `Required Sources`, `Missing Sources`, `Required Fields`, and `Provenance`
          - Added inline explanation that `Expected` is catalog design-time readiness while `Live` is current PhoenixA runtime proof
          - Extracted Factor Engine help/legend copy into reusable shared constants under `workbench/ui/factor-engine.copy.ts`, so later pages can reuse the same status semantics and tooltip wording
          - Factor Engine page now includes its own source selector, wired to the shared Workbench source store
          - When Workbench source changes, Factor Engine now auto-refreshes Availability and clears stale Compute / Snapshot / Ranking results to avoid cross-environment confusion
          - Availability header now shows source-aware labels using the currently selected Workbench source instead of an implicit default-only view
          - Compute / Snapshot / Ranking tabs now explicitly show the currently selected source, reducing cross-environment misreads when operators jump between tabs
          - Registry wording is less ambiguous: `H↑` / `Mkt Data` have been clarified into full labels with shared tooltip explanations
          - Availability now shows inline live-status legends, capability-source trust hints, source coverage summaries, and direct `missing_fields` / `unknown_fields` previews before opening detail rows
          - Refreshing Availability now clears stale table content first, so a failed reload no longer leaves users looking at old source/runtime evidence as if it were fresh
- v0.13.0
      - **Cthulhu workbench alignment**
          - Updated factor metadata TypeScript model to accept enriched Artemis registry payload
          - Corrected factor category color mapping to match Artemis categories
          - Factor Registry tab now surfaces management policy and PhoenixA lineage from the factor catalog seed
          - Factor Registry now shows static availability hints; Snapshot tab now shows runtime freshness and missing reasons
          - Added a dedicated Availability tab in the factor-engine page, wired to `/factors/availability`
          - Availability tab now shows platform summary, source readiness, factor-level live status, missing sources, required field count, and provenance preview
          - Availability tab now supports search, category filter, and missing-source filter
          - Availability table now renders full factor-level `required_fields` and full `provenance` details instead of preview-only snippets
          - Availability table now supports expandable troubleshooting detail rows with longer notes, source-status details, and time-range display
          - Added Availability sorting controls (`availability_status`, `required_field_count`, `category`, `name`)
          - Added Availability jump actions to Registry, Ranking, and Snapshot for same-factor troubleshooting flow
          - Added Source Readiness → Factor Availability linked filtering for source-centric troubleshooting
          - Added Availability `Expand All` / `Collapse All` actions for faster multi-factor inspection
          - Snapshot jump now highlights and auto-scrolls to the focused factor when matching rows are present
- v0.12.3
    - New: Logo added to top navigation bar (cthulhu.png)
    - Fix: CronJob task.yaml editor now only shows/edits the specific task's config section, not the entire YAML file
    - Enhanced: JSONB field discovery now works for ALL tables with JSONB columns (not just financial_statement/corporate_action)
    - New: `PhoenixAService.getDataDictionary()` API method for data dictionary endpoint
- v0.12.2
    - Fix: Table Detail breadcrumb now shows "Home / PhoenixA / Data Catalog / Table Detail" (nested route fix)
    - New: CronJob task edit page shows "Artemis task.yaml 配置" collapsible panel for artemis tasks, allowing inline YAML editing
- v0.12.1
    - Fix: Added `PieChart` import in `app.config.ts` — storage distribution pie chart on Data Catalog page was empty because ECharts `PieChart` module was not registered (only `BarChart`/`LineChart`/etc. were imported)
- v0.12.0
    - **PhoenixA Data Catalog Dashboard** — data asset visibility and management UI
        - New page: **Data Catalog** (`/phoenixa/catalog`) — now the default landing page for PhoenixA feature
            - Summary statistics cards: total tables, total rows, data size, index size
            - Storage distribution pie chart (ECharts): NVMe Hot vs SATA Warm usage
            - Domain disk usage horizontal bar chart (ECharts): bars/taxonomy/kg/financial/strategy/factor sorted by size
            - Neo4j graph summary card: total nodes, total edges, node labels, relationship types, availability state
            - Filterable & searchable table inventory: domain filter dropdown + text search
            - Table rows with tags: domain color-coded, TimescaleDB (TS), JSONB, Hot/Warm tier indicators
            - Time range display for time-series tables
            - Click-to-navigate to table detail page
            - Auto-refresh every 60 seconds + manual force-refresh button
        - New page: **Table Detail** (`/phoenixa/catalog/:schema/:table`) — deep-dive into individual table
            - Overview panel: domain, description, row count, data/index size, tablespace, storage tier
            - Time range highlight for temporal data
            - Column list table: name, type (color-coded by category), nullable, primary key, description
            - JSONB field discovery: collapsible panels showing discovered keys per type (e.g., balance_sheet → [TOTAL_ASSETS, ...])
            - Index list: name, columns, unique flag, index type (GIN highlighted)
            - Data lineage panel: source system, ingestion method, refresh schedule, API endpoint
        - New models: `CatalogOverview`, `TableCatalogEntry`, `TableDetail`, `ColumnMeta`, `IndexMeta`, `DataLineage`, `StorageInfo`, `TablespaceInfo`, `GraphCatalogOverview`, `GraphLabelInfo`, `GraphRelTypeInfo` + related interfaces
        - `PhoenixAService`: 5 new API methods (`getCatalogOverview`, `getCatalogTables`, `getTableDetail`, `getStorageInfo`, `getGraphCatalog`)
        - Routes updated: default redirect changed from `/buffer` to `/catalog`; Write Buffer moved to order 2
- v0.11.0
    - **Atlas Knowledge Graph feature module** (`/atlas`) — new route group for KG exploration and analysis
        - New page: **Dashboard** (`/atlas/dashboard`)
            - Graph statistics cards: total nodes, total edges, recent events count, pipeline runs count
            - Node type breakdown with color-coded tags
            - Recent events table: entity, type, direction, severity, source count, time bucket
            - Pipeline runs table with trigger button: date, docs, events new/deduped, cost, status
        - New page: **Graph Explorer** (`/atlas/graph`)
            - Company search with ECharts force-directed graph visualization
            - Interactive: click node to explore, drag to rearrange
            - Details panel with tabs: Relationships, Timeline, Competitors
            - Color-coded nodes by type (Company=blue, Product=cyan, Resource=orange, etc.)
        - New page: **Events & Impact** (`/atlas/events`)
            - Event list with filters: event type selector, entity name search
            - Impact analysis panel: direct impacts, indirect impacts, LLM analysis text
            - Severity/direction color coding (red=high/up, green=low/down, orange=medium)
        - New page: **Company Review** (`/atlas/company`)
            - Company name search with LLM-generated investment review
            - Graph data summary: relationships count, competitors, events, resource dependencies
            - Full review text display
        - New page: **Document Management** (`/atlas/documents`)
            - File upload modal with doc type and company selection
            - Document list with type/status filters
            - Extract button for pending documents
        - New service: `AtlasApiService` — API client for Atlas backend endpoints
        - Atlas top-nav entry: icon=deployment-unit, path=/atlas
        - Environment configs updated with `atlasApiBase` for dev/prod
- v0.10.0
    - **Factor Engine page** (`/artemis/factors`) — new tab-based dashboard for factor management
        - **Factor Registry tab**: browse all registered factors with name, Chinese name, category (color-tagged), formula, unit, higher-is-better indicator, and market data requirement
        - **Compute tab**: trigger full-market or incremental (by symbols) factor computation with date & market selector
        - **Snapshot tab**: query single-symbol factor snapshot showing raw and normalized factor values in sorted tables
        - **Ranking tab**: view top-N factor rankings across the market with selectable factor and date; factor dropdown populated from registry
    - **Regime Engine page** (`/artemis/regime`) — new tab-based dashboard for market regime analysis
        - **Current Regime tab**: real-time regime state display with
            - Market label alert banner (BULL_TREND/BEAR_TREND/PANIC/SIDEWAYS) with color-coded severity
            - 6-dimension state gauge cards with progress bars (Trend Strength, Risk Appetite, Volatility Stress, Market Breadth, Liquidity, Sector Concentration)
            - Transition signals (Breadth Momentum, Vol Acceleration) with directional arrows and color coding
            - Strategy allocation table (strategy weights, factor weight adjustments, position limit, holding period)
        - **History tab**: scrollable table of historical regime records with all state dimensions, labels, and allocation info; configurable limit
        - **Features tab**: query raw regime features (8 input metrics) for any trade date with color-coded values
        - **Compute tab**: single-day regime computation and batch backfill by comma-separated dates
    - New services: `FactorService`, `RegimeService` — API clients for Artemis `/factors/*` and `/regime/*` endpoints
    - New models: `FactorMeta`, `FactorSnapshot`, `FactorRankItem`, `FactorComputeResult`, `RegimeResult`, `RegimeFeatures`, `RegimeComputeResult`
    - Artemis side-menu updated: added "Factor Engine" (order 4) and "Regime Engine" (order 5) menu items
- v0.9.1
    - Added phoenixA on top-nav bar.
- v0.9.0
    - **PhoenixA feature module** — new `/phoenixa` route group for data platform monitoring
        - New page: **Write Buffer Stats** (`/phoenixa/buffer`)
            - Real-time dashboard showing buffer enabled status, per-table metrics
            - Summary statistics: total submitted, flushed, pending, active buffers
            - Per-buffer table with key, submitted_rows, flushed_rows, pending_items, flush_count
            - Auto-refresh every 10 seconds
            - Pending items > 1000 highlighted in red
        - New service: `PhoenixAService` with `getBufferStats()` API call
        - New models: `BufferStats`, `WriteBufferStatus`
        - Shell component with `<router-outlet>` (same pattern as artemis/cronjobs)
        - Lazy-loaded routes registered in `app.routes.ts`
        - Environment configs updated with `phoenixAApiBase` for dev/prod/home
- v0.8.0
    - **Renamed diagnostics → Transaction Details**
        - Model: `DiagnosticEvent` → `BarDetailEvent`, `diagnostics` → `bar_details`
        - Component renamed to `BacktestBarDetailsComponent` (`app-backtest-bar-details`)
        - Config divider renamed to "Transaction Details"
    - **Transaction Details table improvements**
        - Resizable columns via `nz-resizable` (drag column edges to resize)
        - Shortened action labels: `ORDER_BUY_OK` → `✓ BUY`, `ORDER_SELL_OK` → `✓ SELL`, `ORDER_FAILED` → `✗ FAIL`
        - Added magenta color for `ORDER_FAILED` actions
        - CSV export filename changed to `bar_details_*.csv`
    - **Return Distribution chart** (`return-distribution-chart.component.ts`)
        - Histogram of daily returns with normal distribution overlay
        - Stats panel: Mean, Std Dev, Skewness, Kurtosis (excess), Median, Samples
        - Color-coded skewness/kurtosis values (green/orange/red by severity)
        - Interpretation text box explaining distribution characteristics
        - Available in both Market Data page and Strategy Research page
        - Toggle button to show/hide on demand (default hidden)
    - **Strategy Configuration redesign**
        - Two-section card layout: "Strategy Parameters" and "Data & Capital"
        - Compact CSS Grid fields (4 columns × 160px, no full-width stretching)
        - Vertical label layout (label above input) with 12px labels
        - Bottom bar with Run Backtest button and Transaction Details toggle side by side
    - **Cron Jobs: Fixed active runs navigation**
        - Run ID link: `/cronjobs/run/:id` → `/cronjobs/tasks/:taskId/runs/:runId`
        - Task ID now clickable, linking to task detail page
    - **Industry Explorer page** (`/workbench/industry`)
        - Two search modes: "Industry → Stocks" and "Stock → Industries"
        - Industry hierarchy browser with breadcrumb drill-down navigation
        - Constituent stocks table for selected industry
        - Industry index daily bars table with PE/PB/market cap columns
        - Red/green coloring for close vs pre_close
    - Added Industry API methods to WorkbenchApiService
    - Added industry data model interfaces (IndustryCategory, IndustryConstituent, IndustryDailyBar)
